Title: Construction of the classical $R$-matrices for the Toda and Calogero

modelsAuthors: J. Avan, O.Babelon, M.Talon

Comments: Latex file 23 pages

We use the definition of the Calogero-Moser models as Hamiltonian reductionsof geodesic motions on a group manifold to construct their $R$-matrices. In theToda case, the analogous construction yields constant $R$-matrices. Bycontrast, for Calogero-Moser models they are dynamical objects.